          "line": 43,
          "severity": "high",
          "category": "potential_bug",
          "message": "The new filter uses `AND` with `NOT: { externalId: { endsWith: suffix } }` to exclude calendars whose externalId ends with any of the provided suffixes. However, if `genericCalendarSuffixes` is an empty array, the condition becomes `AND: []`, which in Prisma/PostgreSQL may cause the query to return no results (empty AND is always false) instead of being ignored. This would break the existing behavior of returning all matching calendars when no suffixes are provided.",
          "suggestion": "Change the condition to only apply the AND filter when `genericCalendarSuffixes` is non-empty, and omit it entirely otherwise. For example: `...(genericCalendarSuffixes && genericCalendarSuffixes.length > 0 ? { AND: genericCalendarSuffixes.map(suffix => ({ NOT: { externalId: { endsWith: suffix } } })) } : {})`",
          "confidence": 0.5,
